  "description": "Walter Benjamin (1892-1940) was a German-Jewish literary critic and philosopher whose work crosses historical materialism with messianic theology, French Symbolist poetry with Marxist political economy, and the technical-reproductive condition of the artwork with the political stakes of mass culture.",
